race.comment: THE GAMBLING GREEK (1) returns from a 144-day spell. Class runner of this field whose highlight last prep was a 1.4 length fourth in a $125k three-year-old quality over 1110m at Doomben. Trialling well and only needs to be partially wound up to take care of these. JEWELS STATEMENT (4) will have admirers after her dogged all-the-way win over 1106m at Grafton last time out. Has been very good in her two appearances here at five furlongs. Just needs to slot in from the wide gate to be right in the finish. MISSY NO NAY (5) disappointed at Beaudesert last start. Big chance if she recaptures the form that saw her lead all the way in a BM60 over this distance at the Gold Coast two back. DE FORZA (6) showed the benefits of a 53-day let-up when he led and dominated over this trip at Coffs Harbour recently. Drawn to play a significant role again.
